WEBVTT

00:00.034 --> 00:03.718
The following message by Alistair Begg is made available by Truth For Life.

00:04.499 --> 00:08.463
For more information, visit us online at truthforlife.org.

00:10.645 --> 00:18.413
I'm going to try and push all the way through now from 18 to 30.

00:19.093 --> 00:21.095
And I want to take the time to read it.

00:22.337 --> 00:27.762
Paul has just spoken of how suffering and glory are interwoven.

00:28.194 --> 00:38.185
And then he says in verse 18, for I consider that the sufferings of this present time are not worth comparing with the glory that is to be revealed to us.

00:39.226 --> 00:43.971
For the creation waits with eager longing for the revealing of the sons of God.

00:45.032 --> 00:57.586
For the creation was subjected to futility, not willingly, but because of him who subjected it, in hope that the creation itself will be set free from its bondage to corruption,

00:57.858 --> 01:00.961
and obtain the freedom of the glory of the children of God.

01:02.143 --> 01:21.063
For we know that the whole creation has been groaning together in the pains of childbirth until now, and not only the creation, but we ourselves who have the first fruits of the Spirit, groan inwardly as we wait eagerly for adoption as sons, the redemption of our bodies.

01:22.204 --> 01:23.946
For in this hope we were saved.

01:25.088 --> 01:27.410
Now hope that is seen is not hope.

01:28.194 --> 01:30.096
for who hopes for what He sees.

01:30.857 --> 01:35.081
But if we hope for what we do not see, we wait for it with patience.

01:36.382 --> 01:47.573
Likewise, the Spirit helps us in our weakness, for we do not know what to pray for as we ought, but the Spirit Himself intercedes for us with groanings too deep for words.

01:48.735 --> 01:56.242
And He who searches hearts knows what is the mind of the Spirit, because the Spirit intercedes for the saints

01:56.418 --> 01:58.100
according to the will of God.

01:59.261 --> 02:25.266
And we know that for those who love God, all things work together for good, for those who are called according to His purpose, for those whom He foreknew, He also predestined to begin form to the image of His Son, in order that He might be the firstborn among many brothers, and those whom He predestined, He also called, and those whom He called, He also justified.

02:25.666 --> 02:30.052
And those who He justified, He also glorified.

02:31.914 --> 02:32.274
Amen.

02:33.236 --> 02:36.961
Well, very brief prayer, an old Anglican prayer.

02:37.001 --> 02:48.435
Father, what we know not, teach us, what we have not, give us, what we are not, make us.

02:49.517 --> 02:53.682
And we ask it, in Jesus' name, Amen.

02:55.746 --> 03:02.099
All right, fasten your seat belts and we are going to head for verse 30, all being well.

03:03.342 --> 03:13.963
It's very important when we do something like this that we don't just consider each piece somehow or another in isolation from either what follows it and certainly what precedes it.

03:14.424 --> 03:17.170
And I was conscious of the fact when I ended yesterday,

03:17.282 --> 03:44.142
that I really passed over the point that he makes there, that although we've been brought into an intimate relationship with God and we can address him in such a wonderful fashion, he has provided for his children in a way that includes suffering, provided he says that we suffer with him in order that we might also be glorified with him.

03:44.823 --> 03:46.706
In other words, he's making clear

03:46.818 --> 03:50.924
that the path to glory is a path that is marked by suffering.

03:51.766 --> 03:56.353
When Jesus explained that to his disciples, they didn't get it.

03:57.314 --> 04:03.884
And I think sometimes we, as his disciples, are prone, perhaps, not to lay hold of it as we should.

04:04.505 --> 04:12.978
You remember that after Peter's great declaration, we're told by the gospel writers that Jesus began to teach them

04:13.122 --> 04:21.210
that the Son of Man must suffer at the hands of cruel men and be rejected and crucified and so on.

04:21.230 --> 04:31.080
The immediate response to that on the part of the spokesman on that occasion, no surprisingly Peter, was to say, Lord, that is not going to happen to you.

04:31.140 --> 04:36.385
He thought of his being very good and very defensive, which of course he was.

04:36.445 --> 04:41.490
He probably was unprepared for the way in which Jesus would then address him.

04:41.698 --> 04:45.043
when he said to him, get behind me, Satan.

04:46.265 --> 04:58.222
So for those who are very keen on having Peter as the first pope, that was one of the first interchanges that Jesus, who is the head of the church, had with him.

04:58.543 --> 05:00.406
You can ponder that at your leisure.

05:00.926 --> 05:11.442
But Jesus went on to say to his disciples, if anyone would come after me, let him deny himself and take up his cross and follow me, whoever would

05:11.906 --> 05:19.478
Save His life will lose it, and whoever would lose His life for my sake will save it.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.144
We don't want to delay on this.

05:23.164 --> 05:24.946
I think we've perhaps said enough.

05:25.607 --> 05:32.338
But again, I'm often helped in theological pieces.

05:32.482 --> 05:37.851
by him writers who have encapsulated big truths in short stands us.

05:38.352 --> 05:44.201
