13:28.872 --> 13:46.098
And that's why, when Rutherford, a long, long time ago, writes to a recently bereaved member of his congregation, he writes to her to say, I am now expecting to see that you defy troubles and that your soul is a castle

13:46.402 --> 13:49.746
that may be besieged but cannot be taken.

13:50.507 --> 13:58.717
Presumably he's thinking of the Samus, the name of the Lord, is a strong tower and the righteous run into it and are safe.

